  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of emergency life-saving primary health care service to internally displaced persons and drought affected host communities in Bardhere district Gedo region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is intended to focus on maternal, neonatal and child health including emergency immunization to the host communities and IDPs, building the capacity of health workers through training on integrated management of acute illness IMCI, Cholera/measles case management and integrated community case management (ICCM) and BEmOC which will be done to equip health workers with the required skills to deliver quality healthcare services.
To ensure proper services delivery HIRDA will support two static MCH in Habala Cadey IDP settlement and Qalaaliyow village and three mobile /outreach team to cover Jirih IDP, Buula Garas IDPs, Sarinley ,Haqar Buul,Lahaley,Marda,Bula korman and Buula Cadeey.  HIRDA with the technical guidance of Federal ministry of health, UNICEF and WHO as well as the health Cluster will also integrate surveillance and emergency preparedness in the program so that enough steps are taken in ensuring early response to health cases and The project will provide the fowling activities: -
Provision of lifesaving outpatient consultations, treatment, and immunization services against vaccine preventable diseases.
Provision of health education and social mobilization to community members
Early detection, case management for epidemic prone diseases and scale up in early warning and response surveillance (EWARNS)
HIRDA will coordinate with Health clusters to response activities for maximum impact to beneficiaries in the targeted project. HIRDA shall also coordinates with other local actors in the target district to enable avoid any duplication of services as well work in a coordinated manner to enable increase access to life-saving emergency response in the areas.
HIRDA been the chain manager as well as malaria program in Bardere will ensure closer linkage with this program for holistic intervention to the target beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
